3. High-Performance Networking Code (RDMA/InfiniBand)
While Colab lacks InfiniBand hardware, you can write and compile the Verbs API code used to manage such networks. 
DEV Community
DEV Community
cpp
%%writefile ib_test.c
#include <infiniband/verbs.h>
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    struct ibv_device **dev_list;
    int num_devices;

    // Retrieve list of InfiniBand/RDMA devices
    dev_list = ibv_get_device_list(&num_devices);
    if (!dev_list) {
        printf("No RDMA devices found (Expected in Colab).\n");
        return 1;
    }

    printf("Found %d RDMA devices.\n", num_devices);
    ibv_free_device_list(dev_list);
    return 0;
}
Use code with caution.

To compile in Colab:
bash
!apt-get install libibverbs-dev -y
!gcc ib_test.c -o ib_test -libverbs
!./ib_test
Use code with caution.

Summary of Requirements
Feature 	Colab (Free)	Colab (Pro/A100)	Bare-Metal/Private Cloud
GPU Access	T4 (Limited)	A100/L4	H100/A100
MIG	❌ No	✅ Supported (if A100)	✅ Full Control
vGPU	❌ No	❌ No	✅ Via NVIDIA AI Enterprise
InfiniBand	❌ No	❌ No	✅ Physical HW required
